Anticipated Challenges and Roadblocks
The MSPUS series covers new construction only, not the full home sale market, which is a meaningful gap I will need to acknowledge clearly throughout the project. It may make sense to supplement it with the existing home sale price series from FRED (HOSMEDUSM052N) to get a more complete picture.
The annual income data being forward-filled into quarterly observations is also something I am not fully satisfied with. Holding income flat for three quarters at a time means my quarterly affordability figures for Q2, Q3, and Q4 of each year are somewhat imprecise. I want to look at whether interpolation makes a meaningful difference before finalizing the analysis.
The biggest open question is whether to stay at the national level or find a way to bring in city or metro-level data. My original research questions were all about city-level variation and the current datasets do not support that at all. Adding a geographic dimension would make the project significantly more interesting but also significantly more complex to wrangle.
